Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with torch symbol and Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 27a, 29 or 200, 9? Name Olympos. From same die as 1881,0824.71.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0886)
